\par 
\par Then she was gone.
\par 
\par He did what he usually did when he came up against something he didn't want to deal with. He tucked it into a corner of his mind, trusting he'd work out some solution eventually, and dived into his music.
\par 
\par It balanced him, fed his heart. As close as he was to his family, he'd never been able to explain what it meant to him to be able to hear music in his head, to feel it inside him, then to be able to make it sound in the air.
\par 
\par It was the one thing he'd always had&mdash;and having, needed&mdash;and needing, feared losing.
\par 
\par Until Brenna.
\par 
\par He'd always had her as well, and needed her without realizing how deep that need was rooted. And now knowing, he feared losing her, and what he'd just discovered.
\par 
